    <name>
				<text>10.3.4.3 Exponential form to Cartesian form (NOT IN QUIZ)</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>Express the following complex numbers in Cartesian form</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts_inline">
<li><span class="math inline">\({@3*mult@}e^{i\pi /3}\)</span></li>
<li><span class="math inline">\(e^{-{@2*mult@}\pi i}\)</span></li>
<li><span class="math inline">\(e^{i\pi/ {@2*mult@} }e^{i\pi / {@4*mult@} }\)</span></li></ol>
<p>Your answers to (a) and (c) should be given in decimal form, rounding to 3 decimal places where appropriate:</p>
<p></p><ol class="HELM_parts">
<li>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]\(\quad+\quad i\) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]]</li>
[[feedback:prt1]]
<li>[[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]][[feedback:prt3]]\(\quad+\quad i\) [[input:ans4]] [[validation:ans4]][[feedback:prt4]]</li>
<li>[[input:ans5]] [[validation:ans5]][[feedback:prt5]]\(\quad+\quad i\) [[input:ans6]] [[validation:ans6]][[feedback:prt6]]</li>
</ol>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>The answers here are a direct application of the formula, \(e^{i\theta}\equiv\cos\theta+i\sin\theta\):</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
    <li>To 3 d.p.: \( {@sol1@}e^{i\pi/3} = {@sol1@}(\cos(i\pi/3) + i\sin(i\pi/3)) = {@sol1@}(0.5 + i(0.866)) = {@ta1@} + i{@ta2@} \)</li>
    <li>\(e^{-{@2*mult@}\pi i} = \cos(-{@2*mult@}\pi) + i\sin(-{@2*mult@}\pi) =&nbsp;\cos({@2*mult@}\pi) - i\sin({@2*mult@}\pi) = \cos(2\pi) + i\sin(2\pi) = 1\)</li>
    <li>First we need to collect the indices, \[e^{i\pi/{@2*mult@}}e^{i\pi/{@4*mult@}} =&nbsp;e^{i\pi/{@2*mult@} + i\pi/{@4*mult@}} =&nbsp;e^{i\pi(1/{@2*mult@} + 1/{@4*mult@})} = e^{i{@pow@}}.\] We then apply the aforementioned formula to this expression:
        \[e^{i{@pow@}} = \cos({@pow@}) + i\sin({@pow@}) = {@ta5@} + {@ta6@}i.\]</li>
</ol>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
